---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { CONTACT } from "../config";

/*
  TODO: Logan — starter Terms of Service in plain language. Review and adapt to
  how you actually work (payment, revisions, deposits, deliverables) and confirm
  the governing-law state. This is not legal advice. Update the date on changes.
*/
const lastUpdated = "June 22, 2026";
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Service"
  description="The terms for using the LRD Production website and inquiring about services."
>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 py-16 sm:px-8 sm:py-24">
    <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
    <h1 class="mt-5 text-[clamp(2.25rem,7vw,4rem)] font-medium leading-[0.98] text-charcoal">
      Terms of Service
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-charcoal/55">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

    <div class="prose-legal mt-10">
      <p>
        These terms govern your use of the LRD Production website (the "site")
        and any inquiry you make through it. By using the site, you agree to
        them. If you don't agree, please don't use the site.
      </p>

      <h2>Services</h2>
      <p>
        LRD Production offers freelance audio services including recording,
        mixing, mastering, and production. Information on this site is for general
        description only. Submitting the contact form is a request to start a
        conversation — it isn't a binding agreement. The specific scope, timeline,
        deliverables, and price for any project are agreed separately in writing
        before work begins.
      </p>

      <h2>Your submissions</h2>
      <p>
        When you contact me, please provide accurate information. If you share
        audio, lyrics, or other materials, you confirm you have the rights to do
        so. You keep ownership of the materials you provide; rights and usage for
        finished work are set out in each project agreement.
      </p>

      <h2>Intellectual property</h2>
      <p>
        The site's design, text, branding, and original tracks are owned by LRD
        Production and may not be copied or reused without permission.
      </p>

      <h2>Payment</h2>
      <p>
        Any fees, deposits, and payment schedule are arranged per project and
        confirmed in your project agreement before work starts.
      </p>

      <h2>Disclaimers</h2>
      <p>
        The site is provided "as is" without warranties of any kind. While I work
        to deliver quality results, no specific outcome (such as streams,
        placements, or sales) is guaranteed.
      </p>

      <h2>Limitation of liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the extent permitted by law, LRD Production isn't liable for indirect
        or incidental damages arising from your use of the site.
      </p>

      <h2>Third-party links &amp; content</h2>
      <p>
        The site embeds and links to third-party services (e.g. SoundCloud). I'm
        not responsible for their content or practices.
      </p>

      <h2>Governing law</h2>
      <p>
        These terms are governed by the laws of the State of Illinois, USA,
        without regard to its conflict-of-laws rules.
        {/* TODO: Logan — confirm this is the right jurisdiction for you. */}
      </p>

      <h2>Changes</h2>
      <p>
        I may update these terms from time to time; the "Last updated" date above
        reflects the latest version.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about these terms? Email
        <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT.email}`}>{CONTACT.email}</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
